Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

Summary, -1 because the "rename fails '..' insertion" case, but I think it is actually reasonably close to what we want, but needs a fix in osd-ldiskfs or ldiskfs/dirdata patch (ext4_setent() appears to be the place where the ".." dirent parent inode number is overwritten:

        ent->de->inode = cpu_to_le32(ino);
        if (LDISKFS_HAS_INCOMPAT_FEATURE(ent->dir->i_sb,
                                      LDISKFS_FEATURE_INCOMPAT_FILETYPE))
                ent->de->file_type = file_type;
